ganga/python/GangaAtlas
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Athena:
* Changed splitting algorithm to better respect the filesize constraint:
  - The numfiles constraint is always respected.
  - The numjobs constraint is not always respected. Depending on the 
    dataset, you can get more or fewer jobs than expected.
  - The filesize constraint is always respected as a limit. If a 
    single file is larger than the limit, it will not be assigned to 
    any job. Subjobs are packed as full as possible, meaning that we 
    search the entire dataset for a file that will fit in the remaining 
    space up to the target numfiles per subjob.
  - The files are now sorted by their names, and assigned to subjobs 
    in order.
  - Increased MaxFileSizePandaDQ2JobSplitter and 
    MaxFileSizeNGDQ2JobSplitter to 14336 MB. This is the limit in the 
    Panda pilot, and indeed some data files are larger than our 
    previous limits of 5000 and 10000 MB.
  - More clear logging messages about how many files are in the 
    input datasets and which files could not be assigned, if any. 
  - Add overall dataset size to info log
* Fix SL5 cmtconfig and setup problem in Athena/LCG
* Fix return value of DQ2Dataset.get_content(size=True)
* Add missing DQDatasetExistsException exception in 
  ganga-stage-in-out-dq2.py
AMAAthena: 
